		<div class="layout-item-intro">
			<h2>Correspondence</h2>
			<a class="xsmall link-alt" href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">Write a Letter to the Editor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>
		</div>

		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="1859">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>Lorenzo Milam&rsquo;s essay about progressive radio [&ldquo;<a href="/article/492">A Plan to Change the World</a>,&rdquo; January 2004] mentions his involvement with radio station <span class="smallcaps">KDNA-FM</span> in St. Louis. In 1969 I was a student at Principia College, about forty miles upriver from the Arch. We could just barely pick up <span class="smallcaps">KDNA</span>, and it was a marvelous radio station. Listening to it was a significant part of my education.</p>

<p>I have long wanted to thank those who made that station possible. They helped reorganize the thinking of this Southerner, who just barely avoided the quicksand of unhealthy tradition.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Philip Smith<br>College Station, Texas</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

					</div>

			</div>
    
